# Documentation Size Limits

Keep documentation scannable. When a file exceeds its budget, **split or prune** — do not compress prose to fit.

## Limits

| File | Max lines |
|------|-----------|
| `AGENTS.md` | 200 |
| Every other `*.md` | 300 |

`AGENTS.md` stays a high-level index; link out for detail. All other markdown (README, ADRs, SKILL.md, tools.md, etc.) shares the 300-line cap.

## When over budget

1. **Split** — extract a focused section into a new `*.md`; leave a short summary + link in the parent file.
2. **Prune** — remove redundant or outdated content.

Do not shorten sentences or drop examples just to stay under the limit.

## AGENTS.md growth

When adding a section would push `AGENTS.md` over 200 lines, move the detail to a separate `*.md` and keep only a one-line summary + link in `AGENTS.md`.
